        "title": "Room Reset Lead & Coordination with Signs/Greeters",
        "content": "**ROOM RESET LEAD:**\n\nWorks closely with Signs Lead and Greeter/Room volunteers to ensure the ballroom is perfectly set up each evening for the next day.\n\n**PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIES:**\n\n**Evening coordination:**. After Dr. Joe finishes teaching and participants leave (usually 7-9 PM). Coordinate with Signs Lead on placement plan for the next day. Brief Greeter/Room volunteers on their specific assignments. Post detailed instructions in Telegram Room Reset Instructions topic BEFORE ending session so setup can be done quickly\n\n**Setup tasks:**. Position all gravity chairs according to seating plan. Ensure gravity chairs are LOCKED and stable. Place reserved signs on correct chairs for participants needing them. Verify each gravity chair has correct reserved sign for assigned person. Keep track of each gravity chair—they're limited and essential for participants who need them. Coordinate chair placement across all color sections. Work with Greeter/Room volunteers from each section\n\n**Why this matters:**\n\nMany participants can ONLY attend the event if they have a gravity chair. They may have had recent surgeries, spinal conditions, or mobility limitations. Losing track of chairs or placing them incorrectly means someone who needs accommodation doesn't get it.\n\n**Timing:**\n\nSetup typically happens 7 PM - 10 PM (or later). It's physical work. Requires attention to detail. Requires coordination across multiple sections.\n\n---\n\n**SIGNS LEAD:**\n\nManages all signage throughout the event—reserved seats, section markers, group identifiers, etc.\n\n**PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIES:**\n\n**Pre-event:**. Number and label reserved signs to match seating map. Write seat assignments on back of signs for quick organization. Identify missing or damaged signs. Implement workflow for sign replacements. Coordinate with Group Leads on sign needs\n\n**Daily management:**. Work with Room Reset Lead on evening placement. Ensure signs are in correct locations each morning. Replace damaged or missing signs quickly. Track sign inventory. Coordinate with Group Leads when signs go missing. Post updates about sign issues in Telegram\n\n**Why precision matters:**\n\nSigns indicate reserved seating for medical accommodations, accessibility needs, or specific participant requirements. Wrong sign = wrong person in wrong seat = accommodation fails.\n\n---\n\n**GREETER/ROOM:**\n\nGroup Greeter assigned to work with Room Reset Lead each evening for their color section's setup.\n\n**PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIES:**\n\n**Evening setup (their section only):**. Ensure all gravity chairs for their color section are in position. Verify chairs are locked and stable. Place reserved signs correctly on assigned chairs. Check that each gravity chair has correct participant's name/sign. Report any missing chairs or signs to Room Reset Lead. Follow detailed instructions posted in Telegram by Room Reset Lead\n\n**Why this role matters:**\n\nRoom Reset Lead can't set up entire ballroom alone. Greeter/Room volunteers from each section own their area. This distributes the work and ensures each section is correctly prepared.\n\n**The coordination:**\n\nRoom Reset Lead → creates plan, posts instructions\nSigns Lead → provides signs, tracks inventory, replaces as needed\nGreeter/Room volunteers → execute setup for their specific section\nGroup Leads → verify setup is correct before morning\n\nEveryone working together. Quick setup. Accurate placement. Ready for next day."
