        "title": "Coherence Healing Leads: Ballroom & Outside Ballroom",
        "content": "**Coherence Healing sessions are among the most logistically complex parts of the event. Two dedicated leads coordinate different aspects.**\n\n**COHERENCE HEALING LEAD - BALLROOM:**\n\n**PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIES:**\n\n**Setup coordination:**. Coordinate with HSL on overall CH plan. Manage ballroom setup for CH sessions. Ensure HealER seating is properly configured. Work with Group Leads on section preparation. Verify materials are in position (blankets, sheets, supplies)\n\n**Flow management during CH:**. Oversee HealER entry and seating. Ensure pods are formed correctly (HealERs around HealEEs). Manage timing of CH phases. Coordinate with Medical on special needs HealEEs. Handle any in-ballroom issues during CH. Work with HST on material distribution and collection\n\n**Post-CH coordination:**. Oversee breakdown and material collection. Ensure ballroom returns to normal seating configuration. Coordinate with HSL on sign-in sheet collection. Report any issues or concerns\n\n**Why this role matters:**\n\nCoherence Healing involves 30-100+ HealEEs, hundreds of HealERs, specific positioning, sacred timing, and physical materials. Without clear ballroom coordination, it becomes chaos rather than ceremony.\n\n---\n\n**COHERENCE HEALING LEAD - OUTSIDE BALLROOM:**\n\n**PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIES:**\n\n**Pre-CH coordination:**. Work with HSL on HealEE entry flow. Coordinate with Door Lead on entry logistics. Set up HealEE holding/staging area outside ballroom. Ensure signage and wayfinding are clear. Brief HST on outside responsibilities\n\n**HealEE flow management:**. Manage HealEE gathering before CH begins. Coordinate entry timing with Ballroom Lead. Ensure HealEEs enter in organized manner. Support HealEEs who need assistance (wheelchairs, mobility aids, caregivers). Work with Medical on participants with special needs. Handle any questions or concerns before entry\n\n**Caregiver coordination:**. Ensure caregivers know where to wait during CH. Verify caregiver contact information is accurate. Coordinate with Medical if caregiver needed during CH. Manage caregiver reunion with HealEE after CH\n\n**Post-CH exit management:**. Coordinate HealEE exit from ballroom. Ensure smooth flow out. Reunite HealEEs with caregivers if applicable. Support participants who need help transitioning. Coordinate with Medical for any post-CH needs\n\n**Why this role matters:**\n\nHealEEs are often the most physically vulnerable participants—recent surgeries, severe conditions, mobility limitations. They need organized, compassionate coordination from outside the ballroom. This role ensures they're cared for before, during transition, and after CH.\n\n---\n\n**HOW BOTH CH LEADS WORK TOGETHER:**\n\n. Outside Lead manages HealEE gathering and entry. Communicates timing to Ballroom Lead: 'HealEEs ready to enter'. Ballroom Lead signals when ballroom is ready to receive them. Outside Lead coordinates entry flow. Ballroom Lead positions HealEEs in pods. Both coordinate with HSL, Medical, Door Lead, Group Leads. After CH: Ballroom Lead manages in-ballroom breakdown. Outside Lead manages exit flow and caregiver reunion\n\n**The principle:**\n\nCH has too many moving parts for one person. Two dedicated coordinators—one inside ballroom, one outside—ensure smooth flow, proper care, and sacred timing."
